The paper discusses the integration of artificial intelligence techniques in software-defined networking, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also extensively discusses machine learning, meta-heuristics, and fuzzy inference systems, which are sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential use and improvements achieved by including AI-based techniques in SDN, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the security implications of AI-enabled SDN, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
